snippet.textDisplay: I have but two words....Why? and Gimmick.  'Why' would anyone want such a phone and 'why' are manufacturers hellbent on jamming gimmicks into phones driving up their price instead of offering value.  The Pixel 3a brought to bear where consumer focus is heading.  Now, if you want to build on that market direction, build a 6.5" regular format 90+hz screen, decent processor, storage, and memory, a 4,000+ mAh battery, and a terrific camera for around $500-$600 and try and keep up with orders.  Or keep building these unicorns that less than 10% of the market wants or needs.

Sure it wouldn't be the most practical, but it would look cool and just having something that can be used no matter what way you hold would be cool. Like you pull your phone out of your pocket and no matter what side and orientation you pull it out, you can use it.

We're getting closer and closer to something crazy and fun like that, and I can't wait
